result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan E. Freedy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Nathan E. Freedy is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Nathan E. Freedy was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Nathan E. Freedy was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

01:36 PM 15CM635, 16CM241, 18CF1501 and 19CF122 cases called. Defendant Nathan E. Freedy in court with Attorney Francis Xavier Rivard. Deputy District Attorney Peter J. Rindal appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement has been reached. Victim/Witness statute complied with. Counsel recites agreement. Defendant pleads No Contest to 16CM241: Count 6 Obstructing an Officer, 18CF1501: Count 2 Operating While Revoked and 19CF122: Count 2 Obstructing an Officer and Count 3 Disorderly Conduct. Court accepts the No Contest pleas and finds the defendant Guilty of 16CM241 Count 6, 18CF1501 Count 2 and 19CF122 Counts 2 and 3. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Court vacates the DAGP on 15CM635: Count 2 Criminal Damage to Property and Count 3 Disorderly Conduct and finds the defendant guilty of those counts as the defendant previously entered Guilty pleas.
Court withholds sentence and places the defendant on 2 Years Probation on 15CM635, 16CM241 and 19CF122 with the following conditions:
60 days jail with Huber privileges on 16CM241: Count 6, all stayed pending further order of the Court. AODA and follow through with recommendations. No contact with C.N., R.R., J.J. and/or any known drug dealers/users, except in a therapeutic setting. Restitution to be determined within 60 days. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. Court costs to include 4 bench warrant fees in 16CM241.
Court orders sentence on 18CF1501: Court costs and Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge.
Remaining charges are dismissed and read in. 0 days credit on 15CM635, 11 days credit on 16CM241 and 9 days credit on 19CF122 if Probation revoked.
